9
00:01:06,620 --> 00:01:09,220
Ah, that's a bummer.

10
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:12,050
Then, let's have lunch together next time!

11
00:01:12,090 --> 00:01:16,370
Yes, I'll get you something delicious for you next time.

12
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:22,000
- I have a great memory! 
 - Yes, please remember this.

13
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:24,100
Then, I'll see you later.

14
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:28,120
- Have a nice lunch! 
 - Yes!

15
00:01:38,150 --> 00:01:41,300
How can I made that dumb mistake!

16
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:46,900
     

17
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:52,790
     

18
00:02:01,270 --> 00:02:04,300
Yes, Min Chul. Did you see the photo that I sent you?

19
00:02:04,310 --> 00:02:06,750
Is that the right photo that you sent to me?

20
00:02:06,770 --> 00:02:10,080
  This is not the one that I sent you. What's going on?  

21
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:13,120
  Did someone switch the photo?  

22
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:42,000
Is there something going on?

23
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:47,270
Ah, oh, it's about my work.

24
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:52,300
About the building that you're going to build? I guess you're busy with that right now.

25
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:54,800
Yes, about that.

26
00:02:59,540 --> 00:03:00,930
Why?

27
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:06,280
Oh, nothing. I felt really down when I was coming here,

28
00:03:06,290 --> 00:03:12,830
but I saw you and saw Mr. Lee. Somehow that made me feel better.

29
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:18,430
It's really strange. Whenever I see him, he makes me feel happy.

30
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:20,400
You said he's popular at the site as well, right?

31
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:23,800
Yes. Everyone likes him.

32
00:03:23,830 --> 00:03:27,870
It would have been great if we could have lunch together with him.

33
00:03:31,030 --> 00:03:34,770
By the way, something happened to you today?

34
00:03:35,460 --> 00:03:40,460
Ah, there's someone called Executive director Jang at our office.

35
00:03:40,490 --> 00:03:43,550
- Do you mean Seo Ah's uncle? 
 - Yes.

36
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:48,320
He said he got a call from Park Pil Hong this morning.

37
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:52,700
From your biological father? What did he say to him?

38
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:57,000
He said there is a daughter between him and the CEO.

39
00:03:57,090 --> 00:03:59,150
So please admit her.

40
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:01,500
Why did he say that to him?

41
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:04,310
He can tell the CEO directly.

42
00:04:04,330 --> 00:04:06,320
I know.

43
00:04:06,870 --> 00:04:13,670
Since he called the Executive director like that, I think the email incident was done by him, too.

44
00:04:14,110 --> 00:04:17,900
  I wonder if he's trying to get some money by using me.  

45
00:04:19,150 --> 00:04:21,420
What is it?

46
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:25,200
Oh, this is the mother's room.

47
00:04:38,770 --> 00:04:40,230
Oh, my goodness!

48
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:46,300
Oh, Ra Hoon! I thought your mother was in this room, so that's why I came in here...

49
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,700
Who are you!

50
00:04:50,770 --> 00:04:54,260
Mother, I'm--! Mother, I'm--!

51
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:56,280
- Mr. Makjang! 
 - Let me go.

52
00:04:56,310 --> 00:05:01,730
- How did you... 
 - Mother, oh, I got hit constantly. It's me, Joon Ah. Jae Hee's friend!

53
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:06,300
- Hae Deun, isn't he your company's CEO? 
 - Yes...

54
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:10,800
Joon Ah, why are you here?

55
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:14,300
I'm so sorry about the other day. That time I drank too much.

56
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:17,730
- Hello. 
 - It hurts...

57
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:22,100
I'm so sorry. I thought it was the bathroom and went in there.

58
00:05:22,130 --> 00:05:25,160
You should've asked me!

59
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:30,300
I went in there because I heard some sound...

60
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:34,100
You must have been shocked.

61
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:39,700
- Joon Ah, when did you come back from London-- 
 - Mother, mother!

62
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:44,600
Is your coat made by someone from London? It's very pretty.

63
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:49,740
Have some tea.

64
00:05:49,740 --> 00:05:51,600
Oh, it's the ginger tea.

65
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:58,200
- Yes, because you liked it last time. 
 - No, probably Woo Jung Hoo liked it.

66
00:05:59,050 --> 00:06:02,500
- CEO, have some tea as well. 
 - Thank you for the tea.

67
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,000
- What are you doing? 
 - It's too hot, it's too hot.

68
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:14,010
  - Are you okay? 
 - It's great! It's delicious.  

69
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:26,520
Why did Jae Hee's mom have that dictionary?

70
00:06:27,140 --> 00:06:29,750
She would've not stolen that.

71
00:06:30,470 --> 00:06:33,660
Did she throw a tantrum like the old-time?

72
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:37,260
Did she take it away from Soon Jung?

73
00:06:38,180 --> 00:06:42,510
This dictionary, I'm going to take it now.

74
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:46,000
- No, you can't take it. 
 - I'm going to take it! Give it to me!

75
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,180
- No, you can't. 
 - Give it to me!

76
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,810
- Boo! 
 - Young lady Min Jae!

77
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:55,860
I doubt that.

78
00:06:55,890 --> 00:06:58,980
Probably, kind Soon Jung must have given that to her.

79
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:02,900
She knew that Jae Hee's mom wanted to have that for a long time.

80
00:07:04,790 --> 00:07:10,970
But, how can Soon Jung just give that to her that easily?

81
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:12,900
That makes me sad.

82
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:21,300
Yes, Mr. Jung.

83
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:27,000
Brother-in-law! You always came out to the office even though it's a company holiday, but where are you today?

84
00:07:27,030 --> 00:07:29,920
I already went to the office early in the morning.

85
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,940
Ah, I knew you would've.

86
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:34,400
Why did you call me?

87
00:07:34,410 --> 00:07:38,260
You asked me before about when is my sister's next doctor's appointment is.

88
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:41,100
Yes, I did. When is it?

89
00:07:41,150 --> 00:07:42,760
  It's today.  

90
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:43,900
What?

91
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:49,390
- Call the police! Call the police! 
 - You bastard!

92
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,100
How can you not tell your mother that you came back from London!

93
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:57,300
I was going to go see my mom right after this, but I happen to run into you first. Trust me!

94
00:07:57,620 --> 00:08:03,450
So, people in Samgwang villa only knows you as Jae Hee's friend, but doesn't know that you're Jung Won's son?

95
00:08:03,470 --> 00:08:05,130
That's right.

96
00:08:05,130 --> 00:08:08,130
I get it. Go now!

97
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:10,700
You have to confess to your mom! I'm going to check that later!

98
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:13,170
- Yes, I understood. I'll see you later-- 
 - Stop grinning like that!

99
00:08:13,180 --> 00:08:14,030
Go!

100
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,000
- I'll see you later! 
 - Hurry up and go!

101
00:08:16,050 --> 00:08:18,370
- You have to turn yourself in! 
 - Yes, ma'am!

102
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:24,780
Joon Ah is such a problem. It's totally Jung Won's one-way love to him.

103
00:08:24,790 --> 00:08:27,960
My son is the best.

104
00:08:31,530 --> 00:08:35,090
What should I do with this? My goodness...

105
00:08:35,710 --> 00:08:37,600
My goodness!

106
00:08:41,630 --> 00:08:45,700
Did your part-time work end already?

107
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:51,500
Yes. I'm not working today originally, but I came here, so it ended early.

108
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:53,330
Ah...

109
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:55,810
You can keep going the way you were.

110
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:10,490
I heard that you're going to the doctor's appointment today.

111
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:12,130
Yes.

112
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:15,670
How did you know about that?

113
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:20,220
I do have an appointment. I'll get going first.

114
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:21,590
Wait.

115
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:24,500
What is it? Is the food all gone?

116
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:27,400
No, it's not about that.

117
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:34,430
I want to come with you to the hospital.

118
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:39,970
Do you even know what kind of doctor's appointment I have?

119
00:09:40,570 --> 00:09:42,400
I know.

120
00:09:42,590 --> 00:09:45,080
It's the manic-depression treatment.

121
00:09:46,580 --> 00:09:48,750
How did you know that?

122
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:54,580
When I was hospitalized, I heard what you and Jae Hee were saying.

123
00:09:54,610 --> 00:09:59,420
I heard about today's doctor's appointment through your brother.

124
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:06,500
- That's surprising. 
 - I don't have any other meaning to this.

125
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:11,680
But when I lost my memory, you helped me with a friendship,

126
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:14,600
so I thought it would be right for me to help you with my friendship...

127
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:19,100
- Are you sure you're not sick or anything? 
 - I'm sorry?

128
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:24,300
I mean, you are very different from before. It makes me concerned.

129
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:28,190
What if you lose your memory again?

130
00:10:28,740 --> 00:10:32,990
- I said that in the thought of you, but if you don't like it, then forget about it! 
 - No, wait!

131
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:36,400
Let's go together! There's no reason for me not to like it.

132
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:38,330
Let's go.

133
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:44,720
Nice to meet you. I'm Hwang Na Ro.

134
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,820
Have a seat.

135
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:58,150
Seo Ah asked me for support.

136
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:07,100
You have a criminal record of fraud.

137
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:15,320
I bet you would've thought that I would look up about that.

138
00:11:15,330 --> 00:11:20,220
Seo Ah said there was an unavoidable reason.

139
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:25,840
- I had been living abroad for a long time-- 
   - I already heard about that from Seo Ah.  

140
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:29,790
Why are you helping my Seo Ah?

141
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:32,570
I have feelings for her.

142
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:38,810
Are you sure that feeling is not for Seo Ah's money?

143
00:11:39,230 --> 00:11:41,190
I sincerely like her.

144
00:11:41,570 --> 00:11:46,490
If you see me from now on, you'll be able to trust me.

145
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:51,130
If I support you,

146
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:55,900
how would you repay me?

147
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:59,900
I'll do anything you ask me to do. And,

148
00:12:00,300 --> 00:12:03,200
I can protect you from Park Pil Hong.

149
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,700
Did you have a good lunch?

150
00:12:19,100 --> 00:12:21,400
Yes. How about you?

151
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:25,400
Can I talk with you for a second?

152
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:43,700
I'm sorry that I deceived you.

153
00:12:46,020 --> 00:12:48,080
I was right.

154
00:12:49,020 --> 00:12:51,960
I hoped I got it wrong.

155
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:55,900
Then, you're not Lee Dong Chool in the first place.

156
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:57,420
Right.

157
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:02,300
Then, the photo from my friend was also by you, Mr. Lee...

158
00:13:03,150 --> 00:13:06,470
I mean, you switched it, sir.

159
00:13:07,140 --> 00:13:12,940
- I didn't do that with a bad intention. I just-- 
 - You came close to me with a fake name,

160
00:13:12,940 --> 00:13:20,080
and you changed the photo that was sent to me. How can you say that has no evil intention?

161
00:13:21,510 --> 00:13:23,570
I'm sorry.

162
00:13:23,590 --> 00:13:26,370
I guess it is a bad intention.

163
00:13:27,110 --> 00:13:33,450
I did that because I wanted to stay close to my daughter, Seo Yeon.

164
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:36,200
I am a bad person.

165
00:13:36,770 --> 00:13:40,430
I've wronged Seo Yeon and her mom.

166
00:13:41,490 --> 00:13:45,320
I committed a lot of crimes when I was young.

167
00:13:45,340 --> 00:13:52,360
I never killed anybody, but I went into prison multiple times for fraud.

168
00:13:52,380 --> 00:14:00,810
But I didn't come close to you with a bad intention.

169
00:14:01,380 --> 00:14:03,650
I believe you know Hwang Na Ro.

170
00:14:05,870 --> 00:14:08,640
We were in prison together.

171
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:15,900
Then, I bet you know he got close to Chae Woon with a bad intention.

172
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:20,610
That's why I was staying around Seo Yeon more. What if that bastard do something terrible to her--

173
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:28,300
That bastard, he already did enough harm to Chae Woon. He's doing it right now, too! He's pushing her to the edge of the cliff.

174
00:14:28,790 --> 00:14:32,200
Honestly, isn't this all started because of you?

175
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:38,600
I think you are also staying around Chae Woon with a bad intention.

176
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:44,640
You sent photos to Chae Woon's company's board of directors, and you called the Executive director Jang today.

177
00:14:45,090 --> 00:14:49,420
- Isn't this all about you trying to get money by using her? 
 - Who said I did that?

178
00:14:49,460 --> 00:14:51,470
I didn't do any of those!

179
00:14:51,710 --> 00:14:55,320
- You didn't do that? 
 - Of course not! Why would I do that?

180
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:58,700
Then, is it by Hwang Na Ro?

181
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:02,200
  Hwang Na Ro, that bastard.  

182
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:07,580
     

183
00:15:13,140 --> 00:15:14,870
Yes, Chae Woon.

184
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:18,560
You said I should call you when I get to the office. I did good, right?

185
00:15:19,070 --> 00:15:21,340
Yes, thank you.

186
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:24,000
Do you feel better now?

187
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:27,210
Yes, I feel better because I saw you.

188
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:32,130
But something feels off.

189
00:15:32,150 --> 00:15:33,930
What is it?

190
00:15:33,950 --> 00:15:37,370
You sound a bit awkward.

191
00:15:38,170 --> 00:15:40,670
What are you talking about it?

192
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,300
Are you at the site?

193
00:15:44,310 --> 00:15:48,600
- Yes. 
   - Oh, then Mr. Lee would make coffee for you.  

194
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:51,700
Mr. Lee's coffee?

195
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:56,320
I'm drinking right now.

196
00:15:59,660 --> 00:16:03,610
Ah, I want to drink the coffee made by Mr. Lee.

197
00:16:03,620 --> 00:16:08,430
  Then, tell him that I'll visit there soon to have some coffee!  

198
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:10,170
Sure.

199
00:16:10,810 --> 00:16:15,430
I'll tell him that you'll visit soon to have some coffee.

200
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:20,400
  Okay. Koala, good luck with your work!  

201
00:16:21,040 --> 00:16:23,220
I love you!

202
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:49,440
  Why did an emergency board meeting happen?  

203
00:16:49,450 --> 00:16:56,220
I overheard it from the secretary's room, and it's about the re-confidence of the CEO.

204
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:59,830
  Why? Did the CEO do something wrong?  

205
00:16:59,850 --> 00:17:03,390
  I don't know. I heard it was some issue about morality.  

206
00:17:03,390 --> 00:17:06,770
  - They were talking about something like that. 
 - An issue of morality?  

207
00:17:13,370 --> 00:17:16,280
What are you going to do from now on?

208
00:17:17,670 --> 00:17:19,430
I'm not sure.

209
00:17:19,930 --> 00:17:24,860
I guess I should leave since you caught me.

210
00:17:25,090 --> 00:17:29,970
I know it's shameless to ask, but it's my small wish that

211
00:17:29,990 --> 00:17:35,460
I want you to leave me as Lee Dong Chool to Seo Yeon for now.

212
00:17:37,030 --> 00:17:40,040
Are you asking me to lie to Chae Woon?

213
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:42,400
I'm not forcing you.

214
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:45,610
That's why I said, "it's my small wish."

215
00:17:46,340 --> 00:17:48,420
Until when?

216
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:54,500
Please leave it like that until I can do one good thing as a father to her.

217
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:57,300
So I'm asking when would that be?

218
00:17:57,800 --> 00:18:01,000
I think it'll be soon.

219
00:18:01,590 --> 00:18:06,420
- Instead, I'll leave your construction site. 
 - No.

220
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:08,210
Don't do that.

221
00:18:08,390 --> 00:18:11,120
- What? 
 - Don't leave the site.

222
00:18:11,130 --> 00:18:16,230
I want you to stay in front of my sight, at the site, the whole time.

223
00:18:16,260 --> 00:18:21,460
You have to stay within the range that I can check on you.

224
00:18:21,620 --> 00:18:25,370
Also, whatever you're going to do from now, you should talk with me first.

225
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:33,900
You said you want to be a good father to Chae Woon.

226
00:18:34,110 --> 00:18:35,100
Right.

227
00:18:35,190 --> 00:18:39,710
I'm the one that Chae Woon loves the most in this world.

228
00:18:40,390 --> 00:18:44,490
So, I want you to listen to me, please.

229
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:49,440
If you disappear, I'm going to tell Chae Woon that Mr. Lee, who she liked so much,

230
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:53,600
who makes good coffee and good at sewing,

231
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:58,900
was actually the Park Pil Hong. I'm going to tell her about that.

232
00:18:58,990 --> 00:19:04,870
If she figures out that her biological father deceived his identity and was around her to take fortune out of her--

233
00:19:04,870 --> 00:19:07,390
I wasn't trying to get any fortune.

234
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:10,220
Anyway, how would Chae Woon feel about that?

235
00:19:10,230 --> 00:19:12,999
She wouldn't want to see you forever.

236
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:16,070
Do you want that to happen?

237
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:17,840
Are you threatening me?

238
00:19:17,850 --> 00:19:22,840
Why would I threaten you when you're Chae Woon's father?

239
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:26,400
Will you do what I said?

240
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:31,230
I'll think about it.

241
00:19:32,690 --> 00:19:34,210
Okay.

242
00:19:38,730 --> 00:19:40,510
Yes, Chief Yoo.

243
